<!-- The purpose of this code is designed to create a container capable of producing a horizontal scroll bar to view images on a front end web page application designed specifically via HTML. Note: This code was tested under Odoo 18 Online as the application to proceed with development of HTML embedded code to be executed 
My particular use-case for reference was including a Horizontal Scroll Bar to list my real estate portfolio assets under my overall holding company 
Dwellinghouse Investments LLC-->

<title>Current Portfolio Listings-Horizontal Scroller</title>
 
<style>
  .scroll-container {
    width: 100%; <!-- *This line a fixed width for the container. It is defined as 100% width so that scale is based upon the screen that a user is coding upon and not a fixed pixel count. -->

    height: 400px; <!-- Defined fixed height for container -->

    overflow-x: auto; <!-- Enables horizontal scrolling when content overflows -->

    overflow-y:auto; <!-- Crucial to have this parameter set if webpage should have x-axis scroll bar on both mobile devices and laptop screens. Note: Failure to include an overflow-y: auto parameter will cause mobile phone view to fail to scroll listing of properties that stretch beyond the dimensions of the container. -->

    white-space: nowrap; <!-- Prevents content from wrapping to the next line and maintains on x-axis 90 degrees -->
    border: 3px #ccc;
    padding: 10px;
    position: relative
  }

  .scroll-content {
    display: inline-block; <!--  Make content elements display in a row -->
    padding: 5px 15px;
    background-color: white;
    border-right: 4px solid lightgrey;
    margin-right: 10px;
    border-radius: 5px;
    position: relative
  }

</style>

